      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 133: Calling weak_from_this() here can silently return an empty weak_ptr if UPnPContext is not already owned by a std::shared_ptr, causing restart() to do nothing. The class still has a public constructor and no factory/enforcement in this patch, so this changes behavior for stack/unique_ptr construction paths. Either enforce shared ownership construction for UPnPContext or keep the previous lifetime contract and use an explicit shutdown guard without relying on enable_shared_from_this. For example:\n```suggestion\n        dispatch([this] {\n            if (shuttingDown_)\n                return;\n            stopUpnp();\n            startUpnp();\n        });\n```",
      "revId": "2f2b1b61d5a0475323dbaa3897b4d70fc9b69075",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
