      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T20:27:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 139: shutdown() sets shuttingDown_ before posting the actual shutdown work. Because many methods now return immediately when shuttingDown_ is true, any shutdown work that depends on those methods or callbacks cannot run after this point. This is especially risky for cleanup callbacks such as mapping removals and discovery completion, which may be required to notify waiters or finish state transitions. Prefer setting a narrower flag for rejecting new external work, and let internal shutdown cleanup paths run using the existing shuttingDown parameter. For example, avoid global early returns in internal cleanup paths and gate only externally initiated operations.",
      "revId": "2f2b1b61d5a0475323dbaa3897b4d70fc9b69075",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
