      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 294: The same weak_from_this() assumption is now used for timer callbacks. If this object is not managed by shared_ptr before connectivityChanged() is called, the debounce callback is dropped and connectivity changes are never processed. This is a functional regression unless shared ownership is guaranteed everywhere. Add a factory/private constructor pattern or document and enforce construction via std::shared_ptr before introducing weak_from_this()-based callbacks.",
      "revId": "2f2b1b61d5a0475323dbaa3897b4d70fc9b69075",
