      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 505: unregisterController() now returns immediately while shuttingDown_ is true, leaving controllerList_ entries behind during shutdown races. If shutdown waits for controllerList_ to become empty or uses it to decide completion, this can cause stale state or timeout behavior. The method should still remove the controller while shutdown is in progress, only suppressing follow-up work that should not run after shutdown starts.\n```suggestion\n    std::unique_lock lock(mappingMutex_);\n    if (shutdownComplete_)\n        return;\n    if (controllerList_.erase(controller) \u003d\u003d 1) {\n        if (logger_)\n            logger_-\u003edebug(\"Successfully unregistered controller {}\", fmt::ptr(controller));\n    }\n    if (shuttingDown_)\n        return;\n```",
